Greek Labor Reserve System to Save 300 Million Euros in 2012

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-10-02T19:46:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/greek-labor-reserve-system-to-save-300-million-euros-in-2012.html
Greece  will save 300 million euros in
2012 by implementing a labor reserve system for 30,000 state
workers by the end of the year, according to statement from the
Athens-based office of the government spokesman.  The system, which will put workers on reduced pay, will
focus on those who are eligible for retirement in the next 24
months, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  